lenders.name: Gabriel
lenders.loan_because: I wish to give back to children, families, communities and enviornment. I wish to support causes that bridge health and wellness to our youth and support a more harmonious social learning eviornment.
lenders.occupational_info:
I am a Yoga teacher of 6 years. I discovered yoga after years of professional dance and performing arts. I have always been a passionate individual. I love to learn about the environment and healthy solutions to diet, community enrichment and social awareness. Yoga seems to be a practice that allows me a full lense view of my life, and I love to share that process with others. As an openly gay memeber of the community, I try to support social acceptance and ethical ground work. It is my hope and practice, to develop skills and future practices that support my own self care, as well as educate and support others on their own unique path.

I started teaching yoga to youth, in hopes to connect children to the benefits of conscious awareness. I also felt that families who practice yoga, could gain much from understanding self care as a family and practicing the mindfulness that is fostered at home. In my programs I aim at uplifting the therapeutic practice and creating a fun and safe enviornment. I have taught my programs in schools and private groups, such as foster care and welfare organizations. I plan to develop my program and continue to share the tools I have learned along the way. I hope to one day open a Non- profit Organization to support inner city youth and families with a therapeutic practice that brings their best self forward into their life. I also wish to continue to develop my current brand and LLC entiprise so that I can train others and build a self sustaining program that can partner with schools and other companies. I am currently seeking support to expand my programs and develop the project on a property here in the North Bay Area. This enviornment will be a project that builds awareness around enviornment and community. Our programs aren't just about moving the body in the practice of yoga, we also provide conscious stress releiveing projects like gardening and bee keeping. Many of our tools we share are to support all ages and social dynamisms. I would love to support equality to all races, genders and LGBTQ communities and build a more beautiful world.
